Description.text: The fragmented cRNA is mixed with the hybridization cocktail, and heat shocked at 99C for 5 minutes. In the meanwhile, the probe array is filled with hybridization buffer and incubated at 45C for 10 minutes with rotation. The heated hybridization cocktail is then transferred to a 45C heat block for 5 minutes, and spun at maximum speed in a microcentrifuge for 5 minutes. Fill the probe array cartridge with the clarified hybridization cocktail and place probe array in rotisserie box in 45C oven. Hybridize for 16 hours.

Protocol.text: Mice were fed standard chow or fasted for 24 hrs before tissue harvesting. Tissue was dissected and immediately snap-frozen for RNA isolation.
Protocol.name: Fed Mouse Dissection (Spiegelman)

Protocol.text: The protocol for RNA extraction followed the manufactures protocol. Briefly, whole tissue or cells were extracted and homogenized in Trizol reagent. Following the addition of chloroform, the aqueous phase was removed from all samples. The RNA was precipitated, washed with 70% EtOH, and resuspened in water.
Protocol.name: Trizol RNA extraction (Invitrogen)

OntologyEntry.description: The procedure of extracting nucleic acid from the biomaterial.

Protocol.text: See pages 2.1.10-2.1.17 of the GeneChip Expression Analysis Technical Manual for all details. First-strand cDNA is synthesized from (5.0 to 20.0 ug) high-quality total RNA, using the GeneChip T7-Oligo(dT) Promoter Primer Kit or random primers provided with the SuperScript Choice Kit. Second-strand synthesis is carried out in: 1X second-strand reaction buffer, 200uM each dNTP mix, 10U E. coli DNA ligase, 40U E. coli DNA polymerase I, 2U E. coli RNase H in a final volume of 150 uL.The double-stranded cDNA is cleaned-up using the components supplied with the GeneChip Sample Cleanup Module. Enzo BioArray HighYield RNA Transcript Labeling Kit (Affymetrix, P/N 900182) is used to synthesize biotin-labeled cRNA target. The latter is cleaned up using the components supplied with the GeneChip Sample Cleanup Module.
Protocol.name: GeneChip Labeling protocol for Eukaryotic Target Total RNA

Protocol.text: The fragmented cRNA is mixed with the hybridization cocktail, and heat shocked at 99C for 5 minutes. In the meanwhile, the probe array is filled with hybridization buffer and incubated at 45C for 10 minutes with rotation. The heated hybridization cocktail is then transferred to a 45C heat block for 5 minutes, and spun at maximum speed in a microcentrifuge for 5 minutes. Fill the probe array cartridge with the clarified hybridization cocktail and place probe array in rotisserie box in 45C oven. Hybridize for 16 hours.
Protocol.name: GeneChip Eukaryotic Target Hybridization Protocol

Protocol.text: The Cell Analysis algorithm calculates a single intensity value for each probe cell on an array. This intensity value, representative of the hybridization level of its target, is derived as follows. The bordering pixels of the probe cell are excluded. The remaining pixel intensity distribution is calculated, and the intensity value associated with 75% of the distribution is used as the probe cell intensity. The intensities for all probe cells are saved in the .CEL file.
Protocol.name: Affymetrix MAS 5.0 Probe Cell Analysis

Protocol.text: An absolute expression analysis examines the cell intensity file (*.CEL) from one experiment. For each transcript represented on the probe array, the expression algorithm computes the 1) detection call [present, absent, or marginal (unable to call the transcript present or absent), or no call]; 2) detection p-value; 3) signal (background subtracted and adjusted for noise); 4) stat pairs; 5) stat pairs used. The expression values are saved in the .CHP file.
Protocol.name: Affymetrix MAS 5.0 Absolute Expression Analysis

Experiment.name: RAD.Study[study_id=2380]: Transcription profiling of wild type and PGC-1alpha KO liver and skeletal muscle

Description.text: PGC-1alpha; is a coactivator of nuclear receptors and other transcription factors that regulates several metabolic processes, including mitochondrial biogenesis and respiration, hepatic gluconeogenesis, and muscle fiber-type switching. We show here that, while hepatocytes lacking PGC-1alpha; are defective in the program of hormone-stimulated gluconeogenesis, the mice have constitutively activated gluconeogenic gene expression that is completely insensitive to normal feeding controls. C/EBPbeta; is elevated in the livers of these mice and activates the gluconeogenic genes in a PGC-1α-independent manner. Despite having reduced mitochondrial function, PGC-1alpha; null mice are paradoxically lean and resistant to diet-induced obesity. This is largely due to a profound hyperactivity displayed by the null animals and is associated with lesions in the striatal region of the brain that controls movement. These data illustrate a central role for PGC-1alpha; in the control of energy metabolism but also reveal novel systemic compensatory mechanisms and pathogenic effects of impaired energy homeostasis.

BibliographicReference.title: Defects in adaptive energy metabolism with CNS-linked hyperactivity in PGC-1alpha null mice.
